#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an10.46"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.46:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.46:0.2"
msgid "5. Akkosavagga "
msgstr "5. Abuse "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 46. Sakkasutta → sakyasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an10.46:0.3"
msgid "46. Sakkasutta "
msgstr "46. With the Sakyans "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an10.46:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery. "

#. VAR: sakkā → sakyā (bj)
msgctxt "an10.46:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā sakkā upāsakā tadahuposathe yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho sakke upāsake bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then on the sabbath several Sakyan lay followers went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to them: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.46:1.3"
msgid "“api nu tumhe, sakkā, aṭṭhaṅgasamannāgataṃ uposathaṃ upavasathā”ti? "
msgstr "“Sakyans, do you observe the sabbath with its eight factors?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.46:1.4"
msgid "“Appekadā mayaṃ, bhante, aṭṭhaṅgasamannāgataṃ uposathaṃ upavasāma, appekadā na upavasāmā”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, sometimes we do, sometimes we don’t.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.46:1.5"
msgid "“Tesaṃ vo, sakkā, alābhā tesaṃ dulladdhaṃ, ye tumhe evaṃ sokasabhaye jīvite maraṇasabhaye jīvite appekadā aṭṭhaṅgasamannāgataṃ uposathaṃ upavasatha, appekadā na upavasatha. "
msgstr "“That’s your loss, Sakyans, it’s your misfortune. In this life with its fear of sorrow and death, you sometimes keep the sabbath and you sometimes don’t. "

# NOTE: To western ears, this might sound absurd, and I suspect this is one of the reasons we tend to leave kahapana untranslated. However, the sad fact is that the poverty line for rural people in India today is, in fact, 38 rupees/day, which is 48 US cents. Needless to say, millions of people fail to meet this standard.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.84, sc2
msgctxt "an10.46:2.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, sakkā, "
msgstr "What do you think, Sakyans? "

msgctxt "an10.46:2.2"
msgid "idha puriso yena kenaci kammaṭṭhānena anāpajja akusalaṃ divasaṃ aḍḍhakahāpaṇaṃ nibbiseyya. "
msgstr "Take a man who earns half a dollar for an honest day’s work. "

msgctxt "an10.46:2.3"
msgid "Dakkho puriso uṭṭhānasampannoti alaṃvacanāyā”ti? "
msgstr "Is this enough to call him a deft and industrious man?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.46:2.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an10.46:3.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, sakkā, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Sakyans? "

msgctxt "an10.46:3.2"
msgid "idha puriso yena kenaci kammaṭṭhānena anāpajja akusalaṃ divasaṃ kahāpaṇaṃ nibbiseyya. "
msgstr "Take a man who earns a dollar for an honest day’s work. "

msgctxt "an10.46:3.3"
msgid "Dakkho puriso uṭṭhānasampannoti alaṃvacanāyā”ti? "
msgstr "Is this enough to call him a deft and industrious man?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.46:3.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an10.46:4.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, sakkā, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Sakyans? "

msgctxt "an10.46:4.2"
msgid "idha puriso yena kenaci kammaṭṭhānena anāpajja akusalaṃ divasaṃ dve kahāpaṇe nibbiseyya … "
msgstr "Take a man who, for an honest day’s work, earns two dollars … "

msgctxt "an10.46:4.3"
msgid "tayo kahāpaṇe nibbiseyya … "
msgstr "three dollars … "

msgctxt "an10.46:4.4"
msgid "cattāro kahāpaṇe nibbiseyya … "
msgstr "four dollars … "

msgctxt "an10.46:4.5"
msgid "pañca kahāpaṇe nibbiseyya … "
msgstr "five dollars … "

msgctxt "an10.46:4.6"
msgid "cha kahāpaṇe nibbiseyya … "
msgstr "six dollars … "

msgctxt "an10.46:4.7"
msgid "satta kahāpaṇe nibbiseyya … "
msgstr "seven dollars … "

msgctxt "an10.46:4.8"
msgid "aṭṭha kahāpaṇe nibbiseyya … "
msgstr "eight dollars … "

msgctxt "an10.46:4.9"
msgid "nava kahāpaṇe nibbiseyya … "
msgstr "nine dollars … "

msgctxt "an10.46:4.10"
msgid "dasa kahāpaṇe nibbiseyya … "
msgstr "ten dollars … "

msgctxt "an10.46:4.11"
msgid "vīsa kahāpaṇe nibbiseyya … "
msgstr "twenty dollars … "

msgctxt "an10.46:4.12"
msgid "tiṃsa kahāpaṇe nibbiseyya … "
msgstr "thirty dollars … "

msgctxt "an10.46:4.13"
msgid "cattārīsaṃ kahāpaṇe nibbiseyya … "
msgstr "forty dollars … "

msgctxt "an10.46:4.14"
msgid "paññāsaṃ kahāpaṇe nibbiseyya … "
msgstr "fifty dollars … "

msgctxt "an10.46:4.15"
msgid "kahāpaṇasataṃ nibbiseyya. "
msgstr "a hundred dollars. "

msgctxt "an10.46:4.16"
msgid "Dakkho puriso uṭṭhānasampannoti alaṃvacanāyā”ti? "
msgstr "Is this enough to call him a deft and industrious man?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.46:4.17"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an10.46:5.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, sakkā, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Sakyans? "

msgctxt "an10.46:5.2"
msgid "api nu so puriso divase divase kahāpaṇasataṃ kahāpaṇasahassaṃ nibbisamāno laddhaṃ laddhaṃ nikkhipanto vassasatāyuko vassasatajīvī mahantaṃ bhogakkhandhaṃ adhigaccheyyā”ti? "
msgstr "Suppose that man earned a hundred or a thousand dollars every day and saved it all up. If he lived for a hundred years, would he not accumulate a large mass of wealth?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.46:5.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an10.46:6.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, sakkā, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Sakyans? "

msgctxt "an10.46:6.2"
msgid "api nu so puriso bhogahetu bhoganidānaṃ bhogādhikaraṇaṃ ekaṃ vā rattiṃ ekaṃ vā divasaṃ upaḍḍhaṃ vā rattiṃ upaḍḍhaṃ vā divasaṃ ekantasukhappaṭisaṃvedī vihareyyā”ti? "
msgstr "Would that man, on account of that wealth, experience perfect happiness for a single day or night, or even half a day or night?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.46:6.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.46:6.4"
msgid "“Taṃ kissa hetu”? "
msgstr "“Why is that?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.46:6.5"
msgid "“Kāmā hi, bhante, aniccā tucchā musā mosadhammā”ti. "
msgstr "“Because sensual pleasures, sir, are impermanent, hollow, false, and deceptive.” "

# NOTE: I choose the lesser set of numbers; see PTS for variants.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.85, sc7
msgctxt "an10.46:7.1"
msgid "“Idha pana vo, sakkā, mama sāvako dasa vassāni appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto yathā mayānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamāno satampi vassāni satampi vassasatāni satampi vassasahassāni ekantasukhappaṭisaṃvedī vihareyya. "
msgstr "“But take one of my disciples who lives diligent, keen, and resolute for ten years, practicing in line with my instructions. They can experience perfect happiness for a hundred years, ten thousand years, or a hundred thousand years. "

msgctxt "an10.46:7.2"
msgid "So ca khvassa sakadāgāmī vā anāgāmī vā apaṇṇakaṃ vā sotāpanno. "
msgstr "And they could become a once-returner or a non-returner, or guaranteed a stream-enterer. "

msgctxt "an10.46:7.3"
msgid "Tiṭṭhantu, sakkā, dasa vassāni. "
msgstr "Let alone ten years, "

#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an10.46:8.1"
msgid "Idha mama sāvako nava vassāni … "
msgstr "take one of my disciples who lives diligent, keen, and resolute for nine years … "

msgctxt "an10.46:8.2"
msgid "aṭṭha vassāni … "
msgstr "eight years … "

msgctxt "an10.46:8.3"
msgid "satta vassāni … "
msgstr "seven years … "

msgctxt "an10.46:8.4"
msgid "cha vassāni … "
msgstr "six years … "

msgctxt "an10.46:8.5"
msgid "pañca vassāni … "
msgstr "five years … "

msgctxt "an10.46:8.6"
msgid "cattāri vassāni … "
msgstr "four years … "

msgctxt "an10.46:8.7"
msgid "tīṇi vassāni … "
msgstr "three years … "

msgctxt "an10.46:8.8"
msgid "dve vassāni … "
msgstr "two years … "

msgctxt "an10.46:8.9"
msgid "ekaṃ vassaṃ appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto yathā mayānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamāno satampi vassāni satampi vassasatāni satampi vassasahassāni ekantasukhappaṭisaṃvedī vihareyya, so ca khvassa sakadāgāmī vā anāgāmī vā apaṇṇakaṃ vā sotāpanno. "
msgstr "one year … "

msgctxt "an10.46:8.10"
msgid "Tiṭṭhatu, sakkā, ekaṃ vassaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an10.46:9.1"
msgid "Idha mama sāvako dasa māse appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto yathā mayānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamāno satampi vassāni satampi vassasatāni satampi vassasahassāni ekantasukhappaṭisaṃvedī vihareyya, so ca khvassa sakadāgāmī vā anāgāmī vā apaṇṇakaṃ vā sotāpanno. "
msgstr "ten months … "

msgctxt "an10.46:9.2"
msgid "Tiṭṭhantu, sakkā, dasa māsā. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an10.46:10.1"
msgid "Idha mama sāvako nava māse … "
msgstr "nine months … "

msgctxt "an10.46:10.2"
msgid "aṭṭha māse … "
msgstr "eight months … "

msgctxt "an10.46:10.3"
msgid "satta māse … "
msgstr "seven months … "

msgctxt "an10.46:10.4"
msgid "cha māse … "
msgstr "six months … "

msgctxt "an10.46:10.5"
msgid "pañca māse … "
msgstr "five months … "

msgctxt "an10.46:10.6"
msgid "cattāro māse … "
msgstr "four months … "

msgctxt "an10.46:10.7"
msgid "tayo māse … "
msgstr "three months … "

msgctxt "an10.46:10.8"
msgid "dve māse … "
msgstr "two months … "

msgctxt "an10.46:10.9"
msgid "ekaṃ māsaṃ … "
msgstr "one month … "

msgctxt "an10.46:10.10"
msgid "aḍḍhamāsaṃ appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto yathā mayānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamāno satampi vassāni satampi vassasatāni satampi vassasahassāni ekantasukhappaṭisaṃvedī vihareyya, so ca khvassa sakadāgāmī vā anāgāmī vā apaṇṇakaṃ vā sotāpanno. "
msgstr "a fortnight … "

msgctxt "an10.46:10.11"
msgid "Tiṭṭhatu, sakkā, aḍḍhamāso. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc11
#. VAR: rattindive → rattidive (mr)
msgctxt "an10.46:11.1"
msgid "Idha mama sāvako dasa rattindive appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto yathā mayānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamāno satampi vassāni satampi vassasatāni satampi vassasahassāni ekantasukhappaṭisaṃvedī vihareyya, so ca khvassa sakadāgāmī vā anāgāmī vā apaṇṇakaṃ vā sotāpanno. "
msgstr "ten days … "

msgctxt "an10.46:11.2"
msgid "Tiṭṭhantu, sakkā, dasa rattindivā. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.86, sc12
msgctxt "an10.46:12.1"
msgid "Idha mama sāvako nava rattindive … "
msgstr "nine days … "

msgctxt "an10.46:12.2"
msgid "aṭṭha rattindive … "
msgstr "eight days … "

msgctxt "an10.46:12.3"
msgid "satta rattindive … "
msgstr "seven days … "

msgctxt "an10.46:12.4"
msgid "cha rattindive … "
msgstr "six days … "

msgctxt "an10.46:12.5"
msgid "pañca rattindive … "
msgstr "five days … "

msgctxt "an10.46:12.6"
msgid "cattāro rattindive … "
msgstr "four days … "

msgctxt "an10.46:12.7"
msgid "tayo rattindive … "
msgstr "three days … "

msgctxt "an10.46:12.8"
msgid "dve rattindive … "
msgstr "two days … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.46:12.9"
msgid "ekaṃ rattindivaṃ appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto yathā mayānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamāno satampi vassāni satampi vassasatāni satampi vassasahassāni ekantasukhappaṭisaṃvedī vihareyya, so ca khvassa sakadāgāmī vā anāgāmī vā apaṇṇakaṃ vā sotāpanno. "
msgstr "Let alone two days, take one of my disciples who lives diligent, keen, and resolute for one day, practicing in line with my instructions. They can experience perfect happiness for a hundred years, ten thousand years, or a hundred thousand years. And they could become a once-returner or a non-returner, or guaranteed a stream-enterer. "

msgctxt "an10.46:12.10"
msgid "Tesaṃ vo, sakkā, alābhā tesaṃ dulladdhaṃ, ye tumhe evaṃ sokasabhaye jīvite maraṇasabhaye jīvite appekadā aṭṭhaṅgasamannāgataṃ uposathaṃ upavasatha, appekadā na upavasathā”ti. "
msgstr "It’s your loss, Sakyans, it’s your misfortune. In this life with its fear of sorrow and death, you sometimes keep the sabbath and you sometimes don’t.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.46:12.11"
msgid "“Ete mayaṃ, bhante, ajjatagge aṭṭhaṅgasamannāgataṃ uposathaṃ upavasissāmā”ti. "
msgstr "“Well, sir, from this day forth we will observe the sabbath with its eight factors.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.46:12.12"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

